### Join Logic for Downstream Processing

Use the following joins to ensure end-to-end traceability across report layers:

1. Funding Source `event.interactionEventId` links to Funding Source Interaction `event.id`.
2. When Funding Source Interaction `snapshot.type` is `payment`, Funding Source Interaction `snapshot.relatedTransaction.id` links to Payment `id`.


## Schedule
Reports are generated on two schedules:

1. Daily, from 00:01 UTC
2. Monthly, from day 1 at 00:01 UTC

You can choose to receive both, one or none of these time frames for each given report type.


## Webhook
To be notified when a report is ready for download, subscribe to the `report-completed` webhook topic.
Refer to the {% link title="report completed webhook documentation" href="/api-reference/webhook-topics/report-completed/" /%} for full payload details and list of available report types.

## Download
To download a report, call the file download API using the `reportId` from the webhook payload as the path parameter.
The endpoint returns a short-lived pre-signed S3 URL that can be used to download the report file.

Download API call example:

```bash
curl -L 'https://app.immersve.com/api/reports/{reportId}/download' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -H "X-Api-Key: ${account_admin_api_key}" \
  -H "X-Api-Secret: ${account_admin_api_secret}"
```
